RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PURRFECT DANI set a pressured pace from the inside of rivals, confidently ridden through the far turn and kicked clear in the drive under steady handling. DON'T ANNOY ME raced four wide around the first turn, tracked the early pace setters from the outside, raced five wide through the upper stretch and kept on to finish second best. LA SANTA CLARA was off a step slow, stalked the pace along the inside and raced even late with no closing run on the top pair. TOUGH GAME pressed the early pace setter from the outside and weakened in the drive. PAUL'S TRICKY TALE failed to sustain a bid.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Kenneth L. Ramsey & Sarah K. Ramsey

ENTRY.NAME: La Santa Clara
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow, stalked inside, even late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES FOR MORE THAN CLAIMING $5,000 SINCE JANUARY 20, 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 20, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $7,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE SICARII pressed Great Go Go early on, challenged two to three wide around the far turn and prevailed late under strong pressure. SEANOW stalked the early pace, moved up to take aim five to six wide into the upper stretch and kept on gamely while racing from the outside. GREAT GO GO vied for the early lead from the inside and weakened the final eighth of a mile. PRINCE FILIP raced mid pack early on, raced near the rail around the far turn through the upper stretch and raced evenly in the drive. BACHELOR PAD dropped back early on, raced two to three wide in the lane and lacked a rally. W W SPRINGTIME settled off the early going, hard ridden four to five wide around the far turn and had no late rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEFINE prompt the early leader from the outside down the backstretch, moved up three to four wide through the far turn to challenge, dug in through the stretch run and proved best under all out pressure. DOUBLE O OTTO stalked the top pair early on, moved up five wide near the quarter pole and kept on gamely to the wire while racing from the outside. BUSHWICK BRUISER stumbled at the start, stalked the pace from the outside of rivals, swung wide into the upper stretch to race from the outside and kept on willingly to the wire. POP SOCKS sent along from the inside into the first turn and gave way in the drive. RUDY S. settled off the early going, made a good rail bid near the five sixteenths pole and flattened out in the drive. MY BIG DRAMA bobbled at the start, unhurried early on, ridden inside of rivals past the three eighths pole, raced four deep near the quarter pole and never threatened.

Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 20, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allo wed 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MERGER OF EQUALS was sent outside to an early lead early down the backstretch, was overtaken into the far turn, came again from the outside of Coco Puff and drew off to be well clear under steady handling. CATALENA settled off the early going, moved up from the far outside in the stretch and rallied willingly to the wire. CIRCLE OF COURAGE pressed the pace four deep down the backstretch and weakened in the drive. COCO PUFF rated along the inside, made a quick three wide bid near the three eighths pole and faltered in the drive. SHE SO COOL was off a step slow, unhurried early on to race off the early pace, raced three wide near the quarter pole and never threatened while racing from the outside in the lane.
